Name: Ragnr
Description: This rune symbolizes destruction and chaos, allowing those who channel it to tap into the power of destruction.
Progression: Rune, Basic, Lesser, Greater, Epic
Basic Rune: Requires having succeeded on an ability check or saving throw, during which disadvantage was imposed or were under the effects of the Bane spell, during active combat to attune. This rune symbolizes destruction and chaos, allowing those who channel it to tap into the power of destruction.SPACESPACECorruptionSPACEAs an action, you can lash out at a creature with destructive energy. Make a melee spell attack against a creature within your reach. On a hit, the target takes DAMAGE1-3DAMAGEd6 necrotic damage and must subtract DAMAGE1-2DAMAGEd4 from the next ability check or saving throw it makes before the start of your next turn.SPACEYou may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 1 runic attunement slot.
Lesser Rune: Requires having killed a hostile creature during active combat, while not wearing any armor or benefitting from any spells, abilities, or features granting a bonus to armor class, to attune.SPACESPACEField of EntropySPACEAs a bonus action, you can conjure forth an aura of corroding energy in a DISTANCE10-15DISTANCE foot radius centered on you for TIME1-3TIME rounds or until you end the effect. All creatures that start their turn within or enter the aura must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or have their armor class reduced by DAMAGE1-2DAMAGE for the duration. This has no effect on magical or natural armor.SPACEYou may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 2 runic attunement slots. ADDEND Basic - remove You may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 1 runic attunement slot. ADDEND ADDEND Basic - damage 1 ADDEND ADDEND Basic - add If a creature has subtracted from an ability check or saving throw as a result of a runic ability since your last turn, you gain a bonus to your next ability check or saving throw made before the end of your turn equal to the subtraction. ADDEND
Greater Rune: Requires having killed a hostile creature during active combat while prone to attune.SPACESPACERunic SmiteSPACEAs an action, you call down the power of chaos on a creature of your choice within DISTANCE15-30DISTANCE feet of you that you can see. The target must make a Dexterity saving throw, taking DAMAGE1-3DAMAGEd10 necrotic damage and being knocked prone on a failed save, or half as much damage and not being knocked prone on a successful one. While prone as a result of this effect, the target must use all of its movement speed to stand up.SPACEYou may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 3 runic attunement slots. ADDEND Lesser - remove You may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 2 runic attunement slots. ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - damage 1 ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - time 1 ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - add If one or more creatures has had their armor class reduced as a result of a runic ability since your last turn, you may choose a creature. You gain a bonus to your armor class equal to the armor class reduction of the chosen creature until the end of your turn. ADDEND
Epic Rune: Requires having killed a hostile creature in active combat while suffering from a minimum of 3 levels of exhaustion to attune.SPACESPACEAnnihilationSPACEAs an action, you unleash a wave of destructive force mingled with crippling despair. All creatures of your choice within a DISTANCE5-10DISTANCE foot radius sphere centered on you must make a Constitution saving throw, taking DAMAGE3-5DAMAGEd10 necrotic damage and suffering 1 level of exhaustion on a failed save or half as much damage and no levels of exhaustion on a successful one. A creature may suffer a maximum of DAMAGE1-2DAMAGE levels of exhaustion as a result of this effect. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACEYou may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 4 runic attunement slots. ADDEND Greater - remove You may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 3 runic attunement slots. ADDEND ADDEND Greater - add If a creature was knocked prone since its last turn due to a rune ability, it cannot take the Dash action until the end of its next turn. ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - remove This has no effect on magical or natural armor ADDEND ADDEND Greater - damage 2 ADDEND
